Stock Performance Review on Insurance Industry -- Allied World Assurance, AXIS Capital, First American Financial, and Fidelity National Financial Ventures
        																	
              











 News provided by
Chelmsford Park SA  
Jul 21, 2017, 07:05 ET









 Share this article




























































NEW YORK, July 21, 2017 /PRNewswire/ --








If you want a Stock Review on AWH, AXS, FAF, or FNFV then come over to http://dailystocktracker.com/register/ and sign up for your free customized report today. On Thursday, the NASDAQ Composite ended the day at 6,390.00, up 0.08%; the Dow Jones Industrial Average edged 0.13% lower, to finish at 21,611.78; and the S&P 500 closed at 2,473.45, marginally slipping 0.02%. Gains were broad based as six out of nine sectors finished the trading session in green. DailyStockTracker.com has initiated research reports on the following Property & Casualty Insurance stocks: Allied World Assurance Co. Holdings AG (NYSE:   AWH), AXIS Capital Holdings Ltd (NYSE:   AXS), First American Financial Corp. (NYSE:   FAF), and Fidelity National Financial Ventures (NYSE:    FNFV). Daily Stock Tracker published comprehensive and free research reports on these stocks today at:
http://dailystocktracker.com/register/
Allied World Assurance 
On Thursday, shares in Zug, Switzerland headquartered Allied World Assurance Co. Holdings AG recorded a trading volume of 40,783 shares. The stock ended the session 0.22% lower at $49.26. The Company's shares have gained 4.60% in the last month and 32.31% in the past twelve months. The stock is trading above its 50-day and 200-day moving averages by 3.04% and 7.09%, respectively. Moreover, shares of Allied World Assurance, which through its subsidiaries, provide property, casualty, and specialty insurance and reinsurance solutions worldwide, have a Relative Strength Index (RSI) of 67.53. AWH complete research report is just a click away and free at:
http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=AWH
 AXIS Capital 
Pembroke, Bermuda headquartered AXIS Capital Holdings Ltd's stock closed the day 0.62% higher at $64.72 with a total trading volume of 232,249 shares. The Company's shares have advanced 22.02% over the last twelve months. The stock is trading above its 50-day and 200-day moving averages by 0.47% and 0.91%, respectively. Additionally, shares of AXIS Capital, which through its subsidiaries, provide various specialty insurance and reinsurance products worldwide, have an RSI of 55.11. The complimentary report on AXS can be downloaded at:
 http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=AXS
 First American Financial 
Shares in Santa Ana, California-based First American Financial Corp. recorded a trading volume of 631,470 shares, which was higher than their three months average volume of 601.49 thousand shares. The stock ended yesterday's trading session 0.04% lower at $45.76. The Company's shares have advanced 16.41% over the previous three months, 10.13% in the past twelve months, and 24.92% on an YTD basis. The stock is trading above its 50-day and 200-day moving averages by 4.11% and 14.55%, respectively. Furthermore, shares of First American Financial, which through its subsidiaries, provide financial services, have an RSI of 67.21. Sign up for your complimentary research report on FAF at:
http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=FAF
 Fidelity National Financial Ventures 
US-based Fidelity National Financial Ventures' stock finished Thursday's session 1.26% higher at $16.05 with a total trading volume of 247,664 shares. The Company's shares have advanced 24.90% over the previous three months, 37.89% in the past twelve months, and 17.15% since the start of this year. The stock is trading above its 50-day and 200-day moving averages by 9.60% and 21.50%, respectively. Additionally, shares of Fidelity National Financial, which operates as an investment arm of Fidelity National Financial, Inc., have an RSI of 68.60. Get free access to your research report on FNFV at:
http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=FNFV
