Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG (NYSE:AWH) Reviewed By Analysts


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Monday, 17 Jul 2017 06:00 AM  / 0 Comments




Stock market analysts watching Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG (NYSE:AWH) have recently changed their ratings on the stock. The latest reports which are outstanding on Monday 17th of July state 0 analysts have a rating of “strong buy”, 0 analysts “buy”, 4 analysts “neutral”, 0 analysts “sell” and 0 analysts “strong sell”.  



Latest stock market analyst ratings:
 01/06/2017 –  Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG was downgraded to “” by analysts at JP Morgan. 
 12/21/2016 –  Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG was downgraded to “” by analysts at JMP Securities. 
 12/21/2016 – Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG was upgraded to “” by analysts at BMO Capital Markets.  They now have a USD 54 price target on the stock.
 12/20/2016 –  Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG was downgraded to “” by analysts at MKM Partners. 
 12/02/2016 –  Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG was downgraded to “” by analysts at Macquarie. 
 10/20/2016 – Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Bank of America Merrill Lynch. 
 07/20/2016 – Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Barclays.  They now have a USD 40 price target on the stock.
 12/10/2015 – Piper Jaffray began new coverage on Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 44 price target on the stock.
 05/15/2015 – Goldman Sachs began new coverage on Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 72 price target on the stock.
 05/03/2015 – Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Zacks. 
 04/30/2015 – Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Jefferies.  They now have a USD 60 price target on the stock.
 03/23/2015 – Keefe, Bruyette & Woods began new coverage on Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 45 price target on the stock.
 05/27/2014 – CRT Capital began new coverage on Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG giving the company a “” rating.
 05/27/2014 – Furey Research Partners began new coverage on Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 45 price target on the stock.
 05/27/2014 – Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at ING.  They now have a USD 40 price target on the stock.
Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG has a 50 day moving average of 52.53 and a 200 day moving average of 52.76.It has a 52-week low of 35.32 and a 52-week high of 54.46.
The share price of the company (NYSE:AWH) was up +0.25% during the last trading session, with a high of 49.18 and the volume of Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG shares traded was 100128.  


