Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG Key Developments

Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG Intends To File A Notification Of Removal From Listing On Form 25 With SEC
Jul 12 17
As of July 6, 2017 (the “Acceptance Time”), Fairfax Financial Holdings (Switzerland) GmbH (the “Purchaser”), an indirect subsidiary of Fairfax Financial Holdings Limited (“Fairfax”), completed a previously announced exchange offer (the “Offer”) and acquired substantially all of the outstanding common shares (the “Shares”) of Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG (the “Company”). On July 6, 2017, in connection with the completion of the Offer, the Company notified the New York Stock Exchange (the “NYSE”) that the Offer had been completed and that the Company intended to file a notification of removal from listing on Form 25 with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (the “SEC”) on July 17, 2017.  The Company intends to file a certification on Form 15 with the SEC requesting the deregistration of the Shares and the suspension of the Company’s reporting obligations under Sections 13 and 15(d) of the U.S. Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, as soon as it is eligible to do so.


Allied World Assurance Company Holdings Intends To Voluntarily Delist The Shares From The New York Stock Exchange
Jul 6 17
Fairfax Financial Holdings Limited and Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG (Allied World) announced the successful completion of the acquisition of Allied World and closing of the exchange offer by Fairfax Financial Holdings (Switzerland) GmbH (Purchaser) for all of the issued and outstanding ordinary shares of Allied World (Shares), which expired at 5:00 p.m. (New York City time) on July 5, 2017. Allied World also announced that it intends to voluntarily delist the Shares from the New York Stock Exchange and, provided that the requirements for deregistration are met, in due course, that it intends to subsequently deregister the Shares under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (Exchange Act). Allied World also intends to suspend its reporting obligations under the Exchange Act once it is eligible to do so.


Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG to Pay Special Cash Dividend
Jun 29 17
Allied World Assurance Company Holdings, AG will pay a special cash dividend of $5.00 per share.


